      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 77: `isCallNotification` only checks the notification title, and `isDhtProxyCallWakeup()` relies on `pt`. A data-only call push without a notification title and without/with malformed `pt` will be treated as a normal push, so `connectivityChanged(true)` is not called. The comment says 30s should be enough, but the code path explicitly requires full reconnect for low-latency call wakeups; misclassification can cause missed or delayed incoming calls. Use a positive call signal from the payload fields that are guaranteed by the proxy/client protocol, or avoid making reconnect conditional when the app is backgrounded and the push is high priority.\n```suggestion\n            val isCallPush \u003d isCallNotification || isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage)\n            val shouldReconnect \u003d isCallPush || remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n            app.onBackgroundPushReceived(\n                isCallPush \u003d isCallPush,\n                triggerReconnect \u003d shouldReconnect\n            )\n```",
